<paragraph id="8BE336B9FF9FFFC28809FA44FC46FBFA" blockId="5.[113,646,1420,1701]" lastBlockId="5.[676,1209,1036,1093]" pageId="5" pageNumber="720">
The dental morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5C4D3AFF9FFFC289E6FA44FDEEFA7A" authorityName="Pilgrim" authorityYear="1926" box="[414,539,1452,1477]" class="Mammalia" family="Suidae" genus="Microstonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="5" pageNumber="720" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B928EAABFF9FFFC289E6FA44FDEEFA7A" box="[414,539,1452,1477]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="720">Microstonyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is greatly variable, and has been shown extensively in previous publications (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCD4B48FF9FFFC2891FFA04FD77F9BA" author="VAN DER MADE J. &amp; MONTOYA P. &amp; ALCALA L." box="[359,642,1516,1541]" pageId="5" pageNumber="720" pagination="395 - 413" refId="ref6567" refString="VAN DER MADE J., MONTOYA P. F ALCALA L. 1992. - Microstonyx (Suidae, Mammalia) from the upper Miocene of Spain. Geobios 25 (3): 395 - 413." type="journal article" year="1992">
<collectingRegion id="4998F85BFF9FFFC2891FFA04FE61F9BA" box="[359,404,1516,1541]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="5" pageNumber="720">Van</collectingRegion>
der Made 
<emphasis id="B928EAABFF9FFFC28A74FA04FDCDF9BA" box="[524,568,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="720">et al</emphasis>
. 1992
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCD4B48FF9FFFC28809F9E4FE80F99A" author="KOSTOPOULOS D. S. &amp; SPASSOV N. &amp; KOVACHEV D." box="[113,373,1548,1573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="720" pagination="411 - 437" refId="ref5735" refString="KOSTOPOULOS D. S., SPASSOV N. F KOVACHEV D. 2001. - Contribution to the study of Microstonyx: evidence from Bulgaria and the SE European populations. Geodiversitas 23 (3): 411 - 437." type="journal article" year="2001">
Kostopoulos 
<emphasis id="B928EAABFF9FFFC28979F9E4FEDBF99A" box="[257,302,1548,1573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="720">et al</emphasis>
. 2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCD4B48FF9FFFC289FCF9E4FDD3F99A" author="LIU L. P. &amp; KOSTOPOULOS D. S. &amp; FORTELIUS M." box="[388,550,1548,1573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="720" pagination="49 - 64" refId="ref5914" refString="LIU L. P., KOSTOPOULOS D. S. F FORTELIUS M. 2004. - Late Miocene Microstonyx remains (Suidae, Artiodactyla) from Hezheng areas. Geobios 37 (1): 49 - 64." type="journal article" year="2004">
Liu 
<emphasis id="B928EAABFF9FFFC289CAF9E4FE2AF99A" box="[434,479,1548,1573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="720">et al</emphasis>
. 2004
</bibRefCitation>
, and literature listed herein), and the Akkaşdagwı suid fits well within the known range. Notable characteristics of the Akkaşdagwı population include a somewhat complicated M3/m3 occlusal pattern, and the main lingual cusp of p4 being placed as far forward as the labial one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336B9FF9FFFC28ADCFB84FCEBFB3A" blockId="5.[676,1209,1132,1381]" box="[676,798,1132,1157]" pageId="5" pageNumber="720">
<emphasis id="B928EAABFF9FFFC28ADCFB84FCEBFB3A" box="[676,798,1132,1157]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="720">Postcranials</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE336B9FF9FFFC28ADCFB64FBE4FADA" blockId="5.[676,1209,1132,1381]" pageId="5" pageNumber="720">
Late Miocene suid limb bones are rarely described and figured, making it difficult to supply a comparative study of the abundant postcranial material of the Akkaşdagwı suid. In order to facilitate future comparative work we here present figures and measurements of the material (Appendix: 
<tableCitation id="C6DE0302FF9FFFC28B5CFAA4FC75FADA" box="[804,896,1356,1381]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="14.[113,124,256,273]" captionText="TABLE 1. — Measurements of atlases and one indetermined vertebra of Microstonyx major (Gervais, 1848) from Akkaşdağı (in mm). M1, centrum length; M2, centrum width; M3, centrum height; M4, maximal length; M5, maximal width; M6, maximal height; M7, proximal articulation width; M8, proximal articulation height; M9, distal articulation width; M10, distal articulation height." pageId="5" pageNumber="720">Tables 1</tableCitation>
; 
<tableCitation id="C6DE0302FF9FFFC28BF6FAA4FC6BFADA" box="[910,926,1356,1381]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="14.[113,124,769,786]" captionText="TABLE 2. — Measurements of limb bones of Microstonyx major (Gervais, 1848) from Akkaşdağı (in mm). M1, maximal length; M2, functional length; M3, proximal width; M4, proximal antero-posterior depth; M5, shaft width; M6, antero-posterior depth of shaft; M7, distal width; M8, distal antero-posterior depth; M9, distal articulation width; M10, antero-posterior depth of distal articulation." pageId="5" pageNumber="720">2</tableCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13672A3CFF9FFFC28BD2FAA4FBF6FADA" box="[938,1027,1356,1381]" captionStart-0="FIG" captionStart-1="FIG" captionStart-2="FIG" captionStartId-0="5.[113,124,527,544]" captionStartId-1="5.[676,687,932,949]" captionStartId-2="6.[132,143,1036,1053]" captionTargetBox-0="[118,626,207,485]" captionTargetBox-1="[730,1128,200,856]" captionTargetBox-2="[205,1071,209,984]" captionTargetId-0="figure-950@5.[118,646,175,505]" captionTargetId-1="figure-1031@5.[686,1209,194,878]" captionTargetId-2="figure-1187@6.[174,1157,183,1011]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionTargetPageId-2="6" captionText-0="FIG. 3. — Microstonyx major (Gervais, 1848) from Akkaşdağı, dorsal view of atlas AK5-258. Scale bar: 5 cm." captionText-1="FIG. 4. — Microstonyx major (Gervais, 1848) from Akkaşdağı, astragalus AK4-88. Scale bar: 2 cm." captionText-2="FIG. 5. — Microstonyx major (Gervais, 1848) from Akkaşdağı, metapodials; A, AK5-199; B, AKK-82; C, AK5-48. Scale bar: 5 cm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4665357" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4665359" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4665361" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4665357/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4665359/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/4665361/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="720">Figs 3-5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
